# Anti-slop frontend (always)

Before any UI change, follow **`.cursor/skills/km0-anti-slop-design/SKILL.md`** and **`docs/design/anti-slop-doctrine.md`**.

## Auto-fail patterns

- Inter/Roboto/Open Sans as sole UI font
- Purple/indigo/violet brand gradients or gradient-clipped headlines
- Centered SaaS hero recipe (eyebrow pill + H1 + dual pill CTAs)
- Equal icon-tile feature cards / fake stat strips / glow-heavy decoration
- Default “AI nav” without a genre-specific alternative
- Zebra section rhythm (`nth-child` Paper/Snow alternation); continuous canvas + intentional bands only
- Generic map-pin / padded favicon / purple gradient pin instead of the Origin stamp mark system
- Motion spam outside paint-phase vocabulary (reveals + masthead compact + Offer sticky pin); ignore `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Craft soft-close: class-only / curl-200 / “no purple” evidence without Hard gate side-by-side claims (`docs/design/craft-parity-phase.md`)
- Dark-mode-first marketing, or optional dark that is purple-glow / neon-orb / Nous-only
- First viewport “product proof” that is only a static mock with no live product path
- Italic display / section headers; re-drawn fake browser/phone/IDE chrome around screenshots
- Mid-render token improvisation (one-off hex/font bypassing `tokens.css`)
- Invented metrics in proof bars; `transition-all` / universal `hover:scale-105` / bounce UI easings
- Generic structural fingerprint: hero → 3 icon cards → dual pill CTAs as the default page

## Required

- Distinct display + body pairing from `docs/brand-tokens.md`
- One anchor hue + restrained accent
- Biased (not fully centered) compositions where the page genre allows
- First viewport: brand, one headline, one support line, one CTA group, one dominant visual
- Phase-2 study when touching landing/chrome: `docs/design/reference-study-stirling-satisfecho-nous.md`
- Paint-phase surfaces/motion when touching chrome: `docs/design/stirling-paint-phase.md` (`.surface-*`, `[data-reveal]`, sticky rules)
- Craft / HARD parity FEATs: Hard gate protocol in Testing instructions (`docs/design/craft-parity-phase.md`)
- UI FEATs: Hallmark adaptations + pre-emit scores (`docs/design/hallmark-adaptations.md`)

Tailwind is allowed as implementation detail. Tailwind’s **demo aesthetic** is not.
